events.name: New York Knicks at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Alec Burks scored a season-high 34 points to lead a huge night from New York's bench and the Knicks beat the short-handed Detroit Pistons 94-85 Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burks, Knicks bench power past short-handed Pistons 94-85

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored a season-high 35 points, LaMelo Ball added 21 points and 12 rebounds, and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Indiana Pacers 116-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets take charge early, hold on late to beat Pacers

headlines.description: — Eric Bledsoe scored 10 of his 17 points in the fourth quarter, hitting a key 3-pointer down the stretch, to help the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Boston Celtics 91-82 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Eric Bledsoe has big 4th quarter, Clippers hold off Celtics

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 25 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Atlanta Hawks for the second time in three nights, 131-117 on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls beat Hawks for 2nd time in 3 nights, run streak to 5

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 41 points, Desmond Bane added 20 and the Memphis Grizzlies overcame a 14-point second-half deficit to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 104-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant scores 41 points, Grizzlies beat slumping Lakers

events.name: Miami Heat at San Antonio Spurs
Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker joined some heady company Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker has 38 points, Suns beat Thunder to end 2-game skid

events.name: Utah Jazz at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 22 points and 14 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz beat the Portland Trail Blazers 120-105 on Wednesday night with star Donovan Mitchell out with a sore back.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert, Jazz beat Trail Blazers without injured Mitchell

headlines.description: — Chimezie Metu made a corner 3-pointer at the buzzer to give the Sacramento Kings a 95-94 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Wednesday night in the opener of a two-game set between the teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chimezie Metu hits 3 at buzzer, Kings beat Mavs 95-94
